{{China divisions by}} {{refimprove|date=October 2018}} {{update|date=October 2018}}
The '''[[sex ratio]] of [[China|Chinese]] administrative divisions''' is the ratio of males to females in the population of the particular area. It has been the subject of academic study because of a high imbalance in births since the 1990s{{cn|date=October 2018}} and [[List of Chinese administrative divisions by female infanticide|female infanticide]] further worsening the imbalanced sex ratios at birth.
==Gender ratio for ages 1-4== The figures are from the intercensus survey of 2005, which was carried out in November 2005 on a representative 1% of the total population.<ref name="bmj">{{cite journal|url=http://www.bmj.com/content/338/bmj.b1211.full|doi=10.1136/bmj.b1211|date=9 April 2009|title=China’s excess males, sex selective abortion, and one child policy: analysis of data from 2005 national intercensus survey|authors=Wei Xing Zhu, Li Lu, Therese Hesketh|volume=338|journal=[[British Medical Journal]]|page=b1211|pmid=19359290|pmc=2667570}}</ref>
